-- Deutsche Bank to Close Some Wealth Units in Eastern Europe, WiBlatt Says
-- Zoe Schneeweiss
-- 2010-07-01T06:41:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/deutsche-bank-to-close-some-wealth-units-in-eastern-europe-wiblatt-says.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG  plans to close 
wealth management offices in Budapest and Warsaw, 
Wirtschaftsblatt reported, citing  Bernhard Ramsauer , who heads 
the bankâ€™s Austrian private wealth management unit.  
 Clients in those countries will be serviced out of Vienna
and Geneva, the newspaper said.  
 While he expects the unit to make a loss again this year,
Ramsauer aims for a return to profit in 2011, Vienna-based 
Wirtschaftsblatt reported. The unit, which at that time was 
called Sal. Oppenheim Oesterreich, made a profit of 1.5 million
euros in 2008, the paper said.   
          
          


  


        